  "prompt": "What is the best all round fighter jet as of 2015?",
  "response": "Determining the \"best\" all-round fighter jet as of 2015 involves evaluating various factors such as multirole capabilities, performance, avionics, stealth features, range, and versatility in different mission profiles (air superiority, ground attack, reconnaissance, etc.). As of 2015, several fighter jets stood out in the global arena, each excelling in different aspects. Here are some of the top contenders:\n\n### 1. **F-35 Lightning II (Lockheed Martin)**\n- **Role:** Multirole stealth fighter\n- **Key Features:**\n  - **Stealth Capabilities:** Designed with advanced stealth technology to reduce radar cross-section.\n  - **Situational Awareness:** Equipped with advanced sensors and avionics, including the Distributed Aperture System (DAS) for 360-degree coverage.\n  - **Variants:** Available in three main variants (F-35A for conventional takeoff and landing, F-35B for short takeoff and vertical landing, and F-35C for carrier operations), enhancing its versatility across different platforms.\n- **Status in 2015:** The F-35 was still undergoing testing and entering initial service phases with several air forces. Its advanced technology promised significant multirole flexibility, but early deployments faced challenges related to software bugs and cost overruns.\n\n### 2. **F-22 Raptor (Lockheed Martin)**\n- **Role:** Air superiority fighter with secondary strike capabilities\n- **Key Features:**\n  - **Stealth and Supermaneuverability:** Combines stealth technology with superior agility for dominance in air-to-air combat.\n  - **Advanced Avionics:** Features integrated avionics and sensor fusion for enhanced situational awareness.\n  - **Performance:** High speed (supercruise capability) and exceptional maneuverability.\n- **Status in 2015:** The F-22 was fully operational and regarded as one of the most capable air superiority fighters. However, its high cost and production limitations restricted its numbers, limiting its role primarily to the U.S. Air Force.\n\n### 3. **Eurofighter Typhoon**\n- **Role:** Multirole fighter\n- **Key Features:**\n  - **Agility:** Highly maneuverable due to its canard-delta wing configuration.\n  - **Multirole Flexibility:** Capable of air superiority and ground attack missions with a wide array of weapons.\n  - **Avionics:** Advanced electronic systems and sensor suites enhance combat effectiveness.\n- **Status in 2015:** Operational across several European air forces, the Typhoon was praised for its versatility and performance. Ongoing upgrades aimed to incorporate more advanced avionics and weapons systems.\n\n### 4. **Dassault Rafale**\n- **Role:** Multirole fighter\n- **Key Features:**\n  - **Versatility:** Designed to perform a wide range of missions, including air superiority, ground support, reconnaissance, and nuclear deterrence.\n  - **Advanced Systems:** Features advanced avionics, radar systems (such as the RBE2-AA AESA radar), and electronic warfare capabilities.\n  - **Design:** Omnidirectional capabilities allow operations from both land bases and aircraft carriers.\n- **Status in 2015:** The Rafale was actively in service with the French Air Force and Navy, demonstrating combat effectiveness in operations such as the 2011 military intervention in Libya and ongoing roles in Middle Eastern conflicts.\n\n### 5. **Sukhoi Su-35**\n- **Role:** Air superiority fighter with multirole capabilities\n- **Key Features:**\n  - **Supermaneuverability:** Equipped with thrust-vectoring engines for exceptional agility.\n  - **Advanced Avionics:** Modern radar systems and electronic warfare suites.\n  - **Range and Payload:** Extended range and significant payload capacity for various weapons.\n- **Status in 2015:** The Su-35 was nearing full-scale production, primarily for the Russian Air Force and export customers. It was recognized for combining advanced aerodynamics with powerful engines and sophisticated avionics.\n\n### **Conclusion**\n\nAs of 2015, there wasn't a definitive \"best\" all-round fighter jet, as each aircraft excelled in different areas and was tailored to the specific needs of its operating air force. However, the **F-35 Lightning II** was often highlighted for its cutting-edge stealth technology and multirole flexibility, positioning it as a strong contender for the top all-round fighter. Simultaneously, established fighters like the **F-22 Raptor**, **Eurofighter Typhoon**, and **Dassault Rafale** continued to demonstrate high performance and versatility in various combat scenarios. The choice of the \"best\" fighter jet ultimately depended on the specific requirements, strategic priorities, and operational doctrines of the owning nation.",
